The paper discusses the challenges and applications of simulating large-scale WiFi-based wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of parallelization and synchronization, which are common topics in distributed computing (cs.DC). The concept of adhoc grids composed of wirelessly networked portable devices also relates to the field of scientific computing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms for topology maintenance and mobility modeling, which are topics in computational mathematics (cs.MA) and distributed systems (cs.DS), respectively.
